 the \"sec\" option does not have the \"sys\"\nsetting.\n\nEnsure the \"sec\" option is defined as \"krb5:krb5i:krb5p\".","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"disa_stig-el7","profile_shasum":"3141abf03ebd2fe027f3bc84a35879c56346c7aa00db39f625cb2f1661a8e8a6","status":[],"message":[],"compliance_status":"Profile_Error","finding_details":"No test available or some test errors occurred for this control"},"V-71927":{"vuln_num":"V-71927","rule_title":"Passwords must be restricted to a 24 hours/1 day minimum lifetime.","vuln_discuss":"Enforcing a minimum password lifetime helps to prevent repeated password\nchanges to defeat the password reuse or history enforcement requirement. If users\nare allowed to immediately and continually change their password, the password could\nbe repeatedly changed in a short period of time to defeat the organization's policy\nregarding password reuse.","gid":"V-71927","group_title":"SRG-OS-000075-GPOS-00043","rule_id":"SV-86551r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-07-010240","cci_ref":"CCI-000198","nist":"IA-5 (1) (d) Rev_4","check_content":"Check whether the minimum time period between password changes for\neach user account is one day or greater.\n\n# awk -F: '$4 < 1 {print $1}' /etc/shadow\n\nIf any results are returned that are not associated with a system account, this is a\nfinding.","fix_text":"Configure non-compliant accounts to enforce a 24 hours/1 day minimum\npassword lifetime:\n\n# chage -m 1 [user]","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"disa_stig-el7","profile_shasum":"3141abf03ebd2fe027f3bc84a35879c56346c7aa00db39f625cb2f1661a8e8a6","status":[],"message":[],"compliance_status":"Profile_Error","finding_details":"No test available or some test errors occurred for this control"},"verify-patches":{"vuln_num":"verify-patches","rule_title":"Operating system is up-to-date","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"linux-patch-baseline","profile_shasum":"cc61b517eb1ed91dbb9b09c91b923c9a268d9abd2d315d56d4da259db5fbcf3b","status":[],"message":[],"compliance_status":"Profile